{"parentUuid":"4d79ac2c-6db7-4844-8c57-756a1d0b2d19","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"afb19ee80f80ebca5","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcqifqPoPPkvGAytLsW5L","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is the decisive result. At 5 workers:\n- No-quota baseline: p95 **84.54ms**, 497 rps\n- Quota path: p95 **87.68ms**, 495 rps\n\nThe quota FOR UPDATE read-and-decide adds only ~3ms to p95 when given the same worker/connection budget as the baseline — NOT a 40x regression. The reported 3519ms was almost entirely the fixture's 2-worker handicap (only 2×15=30 pooled connections vs the baseline's 5×15=75), which starves the pool below the 500 rps constant-arrival target and balloons p95 with pure queueing delay.\n\nLet me nail the mechanism precisely: is the 2-worker saturation caused by connection-pool starvation (not lock contention or worker-CPU)? I'll make pool sizing env-tunable (default-preserving) and test 2 workers with a larger pool."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3269,"cache_read_input_tokens":67475,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3269,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccqifp4gcSaU6o2y6ZwAH","attributionAgent":"debugging","type":"assistant","uuid":"deccf25c-3c15-4325-aa4d-222568597956","timestamp":"2026-07-09T02:48:56.848Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"deccf25c-3c15-4325-aa4d-222568597956","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"afb19ee80f80ebca5","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcqifqPoPPkvGAytLsW5L","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Nz1YJqGoW3Qpn31YqBn5wT","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\db\\session.py","old_string":"from collections.abc import AsyncIterator\nfrom contextlib import asynccontextmanager\n\nfrom sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import AsyncEngine, AsyncSession, async_sessionmaker, create_async_engine\n\nfrom src.config.secrets import get_database_url\n\n_engine: AsyncEngine | None = None\n_session_factory: async_sessionmaker[AsyncSession] | None = None","new_string":"import os\nfrom collections.abc import AsyncIterator\nfrom contextlib import asynccontextmanager\n\nfrom sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import AsyncEngine, AsyncSession, async_sessionmaker, create_async_engine\n\nfrom src.config.secrets import get_database_url\n\n_engine: AsyncEngine | None = None\n_session_factory: async_sessionmaker[AsyncSession] | None = None\n\n# Connection-pool sizing. Every POST /v1/events transaction holds one pooled\n# connection for its whole lifetime — including the quota FOR UPDATE lock and\n# the several round-trips inside `scoped_transaction` — so a worker's steady\n# throughput ceiling is (pool_size + max_overflow) / per-request-hold-time.\n# Under a constant-arrival-rate load that exceeds that ceiling the excess\n# queues and tail latency grows without bound (this is what inflated the AC20\n# p95 into the seconds when the perf harness under-provisioned its workers).\n# The defaults (10 + 5) are unchanged; they are made env-tunable so a\n# deployment can size the pool to its own task-count / target-rps / RDS\n# max_connections budget without a code change.\n_DEFAULT_POOL_SIZE = 10\n_DEFAULT_MAX_OVERFLOW = 5\n\n\ndef _pool_size() -> int:\n    return int(os.environ.get(\"METERLY_DB_POOL_SIZE\", str(_DEFAULT_POOL_SIZE)))\n\n\ndef _max_overflow() -> int:\n    return int(os.environ.get(\"METERLY_DB_MAX_OVERFLOW\", str(_DEFAULT_MAX_OVERFLOW)))"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3269,"cache_read_input_tokens":67475,"output_tokens":9322,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3269},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":9322,"cache_read_input_tokens":67475,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3269,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3269,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccqifp4gcSaU6o2y6ZwAH","attributionAgent":"debugging","type":"assistant","uuid":"bd5396e6-9d79-4ea9-bfba-54549d714df9","timestamp":"2026-07-09T02:49:05.255Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
