{"parentUuid":"b0920017-9edc-4e98-a983-902812682d9d","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"afb19ee80f80ebca5","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccqja55miR35Ly9yvLkux","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Coherence check complete and the tree is clean. Summary of the work.\n\n## Root cause (empirically isolated — not the quota code path)\n\nThe AC20 failure was a **measurement handicap in the perf harness, not a regression in the quota `FOR UPDATE` read-and-decide path.** The fixture `k6_quota_load_env` launched uvicorn with only **2 worker processes** (`METERLY_PERF_QUOTA_UVICORN_WORKERS` default `\"2\"`), while the no-quota baseline it is compared against uses **5**. Two worker processes cannot service 500 rps of this workload's per-request CPU on the Docker-Desktop/Windows host, so the constant-arrival-rate scenario queued the excess and the tail inflated into the seconds.\n\nEvidence (15 s @ 500 rps target):\n\n| Experiment | p95 | rps | verdict |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| No-quota baseline, **5 workers** | 84.54 ms | 497 | host floor |\n| Quota path, **5 workers** | 87.68 ms | 495 | ≈ baseline; +~3 ms for the quota check |\n| Quota path, **2 workers** (repro) | 3519 ms | 345 | saturated → queueing |\n| Quota path, **2 workers + 100 conns** | 4356 ms | 306 | still saturated — pool is NOT the ceiling |\n\nThe last row is decisive: raising the DB pool at 2 workers did not help, so the ceiling is **worker-process count**, not connection-pool starvation and not the `FOR UPDATE` lock. Given an equal worker budget the quota check adds only ~3 ms p95.\n\n## Fix (minimal, harness-only — no production code changed)\n\n`C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\tests\\integration\\test_perf_k6_load.py` — the quota fixture now derives workers from `_quota_perf_workers()`, which defaults to the baseline worker count (5) instead of a hardcoded 2, so AC20 is an apples-to-apples measurement. The old 2-worker rationale (max_connections) no longer applies: the Postgres testcontainer runs `max_connections=300` and the perf fixtures tear down sequentially (75 conns ≪ 300). The strict-enforcement invariant (usage ≤ L) is untouched — `quotas_repo`, `events_service`, and the engine config are unchanged. A pool-tunability experiment in `src\\db\\session.py` was **fully reverted** (its `M` status is pre-existing U-03 work, net-zero from me).\n\n## Proof\n\n- After fix, clean env (default now 5 workers): **p95 112.42 ms, 497 rps, all 201** — target throughput met, p95 in the same ~85–112 ms band as the baseline, versus the 3519 ms saturated repro.\n- Regression guard `test_ac20_quota_perf_fixture_matches_baseline_worker_budget` (fast, Docker-free): passes after (`5 >= 5`); **fails-before** demonstrated in a scratchpad copy against the old default (`2 >= 5` → AssertionError), never by reverting the real tree.\n- No stray probes; scratch files live only in the session scratchpad.\n\n## Escalation to the human (I did NOT reinterpret AC20)\n\nEven after the fix, the literal **p95 < 50 ms budget is still not met (~87–112 ms) — but neither is the no-quota baseline (~84 ms)**. The 50 ms floor is unachievable on this Docker-Desktop/Windows host regardless of code (`host.docker.internal` + Windows networking overhead — the pre-existing feature-1 deferred finding). The quota path does not blow the *existing* budget relative to baseline, which is AC20's stated intent. Whether the absolute 50 ms threshold should stand on this host, be re-measured on production-class infra (ECS→RDS same-AZ round-trips are ~1 ms, not tens of ms), or be adjusted is a **budget decision for the human**. I left the AC20 test asserting `sample_count > 0` (honest measurement) rather than hardcoding a 50 ms assertion that would fail forever here.\n\nFull hypothesis log is appended at `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\debug-notes.md`; `remediation` retry count incremented to 1 in `.pipeline\\state.json`."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":629,"cache_read_input_tokens":110919,"output_tokens":2546,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":629},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":2546,"cache_read_input_tokens":110919,"cache_creation_input_tokens":629,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":629,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccqja2x2Z78ssSj2QKP96","attributionAgent":"debugging","type":"assistant","uuid":"071a57ff-23d1-47ce-bd59-41f69773346e","timestamp":"2026-07-09T02:59:20.351Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
